---

## 🔄 Complete Data Flow (File-to-File)

### Step 1: User Uploads One or More PDFs

**File:** `client/src/components/PdfUpload.tsx` (new component)

```
User selects 1–5 PDF files → FormData with multiple files → POST /api/upload-pdf
```

| What | Detail |
|---|---|
| Input select | `<input type="file" accept=".pdf" multiple />` |
| FormData | All files appended under field name `"pdfs"` |
| Scenarios | **Batch**: select 3 files at once → 1 request with 3 files |
|           | **Incremental**: upload 1 now, upload 2 more later → 2 separate requests, all accumulate in the same session |

---

### Step 2: Multer Receives Multiple Files

**File:** `server/middleware/upload.ts`

```typescript
// KEY CHANGE: .array('pdfs', 5) instead of .single('pdf')
multer({
  storage: multer.memoryStorage(),
  limits: { fileSize: 10 * 1024 * 1024 },  // 10MB per file
  fileFilter: onlyPDF
}).array('pdfs', 5)   // max 5 files per request
```

| What | Detail |
|---|---|
| Method | `multer.array('pdfs', 5)` — accepts up to 5 files per request |
| Result | `req.files` is an **array of file objects**, each with `.buffer` and `.originalname` |

---

### Step 3: Loop Through Files, Parse Each

**File:** `server/controllers/pdfController.ts` → `handleUpload()`

```typescript
async function handleUpload(req, res) {
  const files = req.files;           // Array of uploaded files
  const sessionId = req.session.id;

  // Get or create session entry
  let session = sessionStore.get(sessionId);
  if (!session) {
    session = { documents: [], createdAt: Date.now() };
  }

  const newDocs = [];

  for (const file of files) {
    const pdfData = await pdfParse(file.buffer);

    const doc = {
      id: uuid(),                       // unique doc ID
      fileName: file.originalname,      // "physics.pdf"
      text: pdfData.text,               // extracted text
      pageCount: pdfData.numpages,      // page count
      uploadedAt: Date.now()
    };

    session.documents.push(doc);        // ADD to array (not replace!)
    newDocs.push({ id: doc.id, fileName: doc.fileName, pageCount: doc.pageCount });
  }

  sessionStore.set(sessionId, session);

  res.json({ success: true, newDocuments: newDocs, totalDocuments: session.documents.length });
}
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Key behavior**: `session.documents.push(doc)` — each upload **appends** to the existing array. Uploading again doesn't overwrite previous PDFs. They accumulate.

---

### Step 4: User Asks a Question → All Documents Used as Context

**File:** `server/controllers/pdfController.ts` → `handleAsk()`

```typescript
async function handleAsk(req, res) {
  const session = sessionStore.get(req.session.id);
  if (!session || session.documents.length === 0) {
    return res.status(400).json({ error: "No documents uploaded" });
  }

  // COMBINE all document texts into one context
  const combinedContext = session.documents
    .map(doc => `--- ${doc.fileName} ---\n${doc.text}`)
    .join('\n\n');

  const question = req.body.question;

  // Later: combinedContext → ScaleDown (compress) → LLM → answer
}
```

| What | Detail |
|---|---|
| 1 PDF uploaded | Context = text from that 1 PDF |
| 3 PDFs uploaded | Context = text from all 3, separated by filename headers |
| ScaleDown role | Compress this combined context before sending to LLM (keeps things fast & cheap) |

---

### Step 5: User Can Remove a Specific Document

**File:** `server/controllers/pdfController.ts` → `handleRemoveDoc()`

```typescript
async function handleRemoveDoc(req, res) {
  const session = sessionStore.get(req.session.id);
  const docId = req.params.docId;

  session.documents = session.documents.filter(d => d.id !== docId);
  sessionStore.set(req.session.id, session);

  res.json({ success: true, remainingDocuments: session.documents.map(d => ({ id: d.id, fileName: d.fileName })) });
}
```

---

### Step 6: Session Cleanup (Same 3 Triggers)

**File:** `server/utils/sessionStore.ts`

| Trigger | What Gets Deleted |
|---|---|
| **Tab close** | ALL documents for that session |
| **Timeout (30 min)** | ALL documents for expired sessions |
| **Manual end** | ALL documents for that session |

```typescript
// Auto-cleanup: delete entire session (all docs) if older than 30 min
setInterval(() => {
  const now = Date.now();
  for (const [id, session] of store.entries()) {
    if (now - session.createdAt > 30 * 60 * 1000) {
      store.delete(id);   // wipes ALL documents for this session
    }
  }
}, 5 * 60 * 1000);
```

---

## 📊 Updated API Endpoints

| Endpoint | Method | Request | Response |
|---|---|---|---|
| `/api/upload-pdf` | POST | `FormData` with `pdfs` field (1–5 files) | `{ success, newDocuments: [{id, fileName, pageCount}], totalDocuments }` |
| `/api/ask` | POST | `{ question: string }` | `{ answer: string, tokenStats: {...} }` |
| `/api/document/:docId` | DELETE | (docId in URL, sessionId from cookie) | `{ success, remainingDocuments: [...] }` |
| `/api/end-session` | POST | (sessionId from cookie) | `{ success: true }` |
| `/api/session-status` | GET | (sessionId from cookie) | `{ hasDocuments: boolean, documents: [{id, fileName, pageCount}] }` |

---

