The frontend needs a small UI to show uploaded documents:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  📎 Uploaded Documents                  │
│                                         │
│  📄 physics.pdf (45 pages)        [✕]   │
│  📄 chemistry.pdf (30 pages)      [✕]   │
│  📄 math.pdf (60 pages)           [✕]   │
│                                         │
│  [+ Upload More]                        │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

This could live in the **Sidebar** or as a panel above the chat input.

---

## ⚠️ RAM Usage with Multiple PDFs

| Scenario | Estimated Memory |
|---|---|
| 1 user, 1 PDF (100 pages) | ~300 KB |
| 1 user, 5 PDFs (500 pages total) | ~1.5 MB |
| 50 concurrent users, 3 PDFs each | ~75 MB |
| 100 concurrent users, 5 PDFs each | ~150 MB |

> [!TIP]
> Even with 100 users each uploading 5 PDFs, we're at ~150 MB RAM. Totally fine for a typical server. The 30-minute auto-cleanup keeps memory from growing indefinitely.

> [!WARNING]
> **Per-request limit**: Max 5 files per upload request, 10 MB each. This prevents abuse. You can adjust the `5` in `multer.array('pdfs', 5)` if needed, but total files per session should also have a sensible cap (e.g., 10).
